---
import UseCase from '../../../UseCase.astro';
import UseCaseInteractive from '../../../UseCaseInteractive.astro';
import Usage from '../../../Usage.astro';
import UsageItem from '../../../UsageItem.astro';
---

<UseCase
  title="Make Responsibility Explicit"
  description="Clearly state who is accountable for the AI's behavior and outcomes—the provider, the deployer, or the user—so users know whom to hold responsible and where to turn for support."
>
  <UseCaseInteractive clsHeight={112} label="Make responsibility explicit" toggle>
    <div class="grid gap-600 w-full">
      <div class="grid gap-400 p-600 rounded-lg bg-tone-neutral-09 border border-tone-neutral-03">
        <div class="grid gap-200">
          <mds-text typography="label"><b>Clear Ownership in UI</b></mds-text>
          <mds-text typography="body"
            >This suggestion is provided by [Product Name]. You decide whether to apply it. For
            questions or issues, contact support@company.com or see our Responsible AI statement.</mds-text
          >
          <mds-text typography="caption" class="text-tone-neutral-05"
            >User sees who provides the AI, that they remain in control, and where to get help.</mds-text
          >
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="grid gap-400 p-600 rounded-lg bg-tone-neutral-09 border border-tone-neutral-03">
        <div class="grid gap-200">
          <mds-text typography="label"><b>Decision Ownership</b></mds-text>
          <mds-text typography="body"
            >Recommendation: Approve. This is a suggestion only; you are responsible for the final
            decision. [Approve] [Reject] [Get help]</mds-text
          >
          <mds-text typography="caption" class="text-tone-neutral-05"
            >Makes clear that the human is the decision-maker; the AI supports, not replaces,
            accountability.</mds-text
          >
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="grid gap-400 p-600 rounded-lg bg-status-error-10 border border-status-error-03">
        <div class="grid gap-200">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-200">
            <mds-icon name="mi/outline/error" class="text-status-error-05"></mds-icon>
            <mds-text typography="label"><b>Unclear Responsibility (Problematic)</b></mds-text>
          </div>
          <mds-text typography="body"
            >AI output with no indication of who provides it, who is accountable for errors, or how
            to escalate. "Powered by AI" with no link to terms, support, or governance.</mds-text
          >
          <mds-text typography="caption" class="text-status-error-06"
            >Users don't know who to hold responsible or where to turn when something goes wrong.</mds-text
          >
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </UseCaseInteractive>
  <Usage>
    <UsageItem variant="do">
      State who provides the AI, who is accountable for outcomes, and how to get support or
      escalate.
    </UsageItem>
    <UsageItem variant="dont">
      Present AI output without indicating provider, accountability, or path to support.
    </UsageItem>
    <UsageItem variant="do">
      Clarify that the user (or designated role) is responsible for the final decision when the AI
      suggests one.
    </UsageItem>
    <UsageItem variant="dont">
      Imply that the AI or the system alone is responsible for decisions that have human
      consequences.
    </UsageItem>
  </Usage>
</UseCase>
